message.content:
1. The results are reported for 2,159 BARI 2D participants.
2. 70% of the BARI 2D participants are males.
3. All reported participants have valid baseline.
4. All reported participants have at least one follow-up MNSI score.
5. The mean age of the participants is 62 years.
6. The standard deviation of the participants' age is 9 years.
7. The mean HbA1c level of the participants is 7.7%.
8. The standard deviation of the participants' HbA1c level is 1.6%.
9. The mean duration of diabetes among the participants is 10 years.
10. The standard deviation of the diabetes duration among the participants is 9 years.

messages.content:
Statement: Results are reported for 2,159 BARI 2D participants (70% males) with valid baseline and at least one follow-up MNSI score (mean age 62 ± 9 years, mean HbA1c 7.7 ± 1.6%, diabetes duration 10 ± 9 years).
